ğŸ­ Real-World Story
A small training institute wants to digitalize how it manages:

Students

Courses

Which students are enrolled in which courses

Currently, everything is written in notebooks. This causes problems such as:

Duplicate enrollments

Losing track of which student joined which course

Difficulty updating or removing records

You are asked to build a console-based application using an MVC-like layered architecture, where files act as the database.

ğŸ§± System Overview
The system must manage two core entities (models):

âœ… Model 1: Student
âœ… Model 2: Course
And a relationship between them:
â¡ Enrollment (Student â†” Course)

ğŸ“¦ Models (Data Objects)
ğŸ§‘ Student Model
